{"word":"μητρόθεν","slug":"μητρόθεν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μητρόθεν</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μήτηρ'><el>μήτηρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>from the mother, by the mother's side</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>from one's mother, from one's mother's hand</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>from one's mother's womb</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}